1,1,1,2-Tetrachloroethane.label: 1,1,1,2-Tetrachloroethane
1,1,1,2-Tetrachloroethane.description: 1,1,1,2-Tetrachloroethane is a chlorinated hydrocarbon. It is a colorless liquid with a sweet chloroform-like odor. It is used as a solvent and in the production of wood stains and varnishes. Wikipedia

1,2-Dichloroethane.label: 1,2-Dichloroethane
1,2-Dichloroethane.description: The chemical compound 1,2-dichloroethane commonly known by its old name of ethylene dichloride, is a chlorinated hydrocarbon, mainly used to produce vinyl chloride monomer, the major precursor for PVC production. Wikipedia

1,3,5-Trioxane.label: 1,3,5-Trioxane
1,3,5-Trioxane.description: 1,3,5-Trioxane, sometimes also called trioxane or trioxin, is a chemical compound with molecular formula C3H6O3. Wikipedia

1,4-Dioxin.label: 1,4-Dioxin
1,4-Dioxin.description: 1,4-Dioxin is a heterocyclic, organic, antiaromatic compound with the chemical formula C4H4O2. There is an isomeric form of 1,4-dioxin, 1,2-dioxin. 1,2-Dioxin is very unstable due to its peroxide-like characteristics. Wikipedia

1,5-Pentanediol.label: 1,5-Pentanediol
1,5-Pentanediol.description: 1,5-Pentanediol is the organic compound with the formula HOCH2CH2CH2CH2CH2OH. Like other diols, this viscous colourless liquid is used as plasticizer and also forms polyesters that are used as emulsifying agents and resin intermediates. Wikipedia

1-Heptanol.label: 1-Heptanol
1-Heptanol.description: 1-Heptanol is an alcohol with a seven carbon chain and the structural formula of CH3(CH2)6OH. It is a clear colorless liquid that is very slightly soluble in water, but miscible with ether and ethanol. Wikipedia

1-Decanol.label: 1-Decanol
1-Decanol.description: 1-Decanol is a straight chain fatty alcohol with ten carbon atoms and the molecular formula C10H21OH. It is a colorless viscous liquid that is insoluble in water and has a strong odor. The interfacial tension against water at 20 °C is 8.97 mN/m. Wikipedia

1-Hexanol.label: 1-Hexanol
1-Hexanol.description: 1-Hexanol is an organic alcohol with a six-carbon chain and a condensed structural formula of CH3(CH2)5OH. This colorless liquid is slightly soluble in water, but miscible with ether and ethanol. Wikipedia

1-Methylnaphthalene.label: 1-Methylnaphthalene
1-Methylnaphthalene.description: 1-Methylnaphthalene is a polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon. It has a cetane number of zero, and was previously used as the lower reference for cetane number. Wikipedia

1-Naphthol.label: 1-Naphthol
1-Naphthol.description: 1-Naphthol, or α-naphthol, is a fluorescent organic compound with the formula C10H7OH. It is a white solid. It is an isomer of 2-naphthol differing by the location of the hydroxyl group on the naphthalene ring. Wikipedia

1-Propanol.label: Propyl alcohol
1-Propanol.description: 1-Propanol is a primary alcohol with the formula CH3CH2CH2OH. This colorless liquid is also known as propan-1-ol, 1-propyl alcohol, n-propyl alcohol, n-propanol, or simply propanol. It is an isomer of isopropanol. Wikipedia

1-Pentanol.label: 1-Pentanol
1-Pentanol.description: 1-Pentanol, is an alcohol with five carbon atoms and the molecular formula C5H12O. 1-Pentanol is a colorless liquid with an unpleasant aroma. There are 8 alcohols with this molecular formula. Wikipedia

2,5-Dimethoxy-4-methylamphetamine.label: 2,5-Dimethoxy-4-methylamphetamine
2,5-Dimethoxy-4-methylamphetamine.description: 2,5-Dimethoxy-4-methylamphetamine is a psychedelic and a substituted amphetamine. It was first synthesized by Alexander Shulgin, and later reported in his book PiHKAL A Chemical Love Story. Wikipedia

2-Butanol.label: 2-Butanol
2-Butanol.description: 2-Butanol, or sec-butanol, is an organic compound with formula CH3CHCH2CH3. This secondary alcohol is a flammable, colorless liquid that is soluble in 3 parts water and completely miscible with polar ... Wikipedia

2-Ethylhexanol.label: 2-Ethylhexanol
2-Ethylhexanol.description: 2-Ethylhexanol is a fatty alcohol, an organic compound is a branched, eight-carbon chiral alcohol. It is a colorless liquid that is poorly soluble in water but soluble in most organic solvents. Wikipedia

2-Naphthol.label: 2-Naphthol
2-Naphthol.description: 2-Naphthol, or β-naphthol, is a fluorescent colorless crystalline solid with the formula C10H7OH. It is an isomer of 1-naphthol, differing by the location of the hydroxyl group on naphthalene. Wikipedia

6-Phosphogluconic acid.label: 6-Phosphogluconic acid
6-Phosphogluconic acid.description:
6-Phosphogluconic acid is an intermediate in the pentose phosphate pathway and the Entner–Doudoroff pathway.
It is formed by 6-phosphogluconolactonase, and acted upon by phosphogluconate dehydrogenase to produce ribulose 5-phosphate. Wikipedia

7-Dehydrocholesterol.label: 7-Dehydrocholesterol
7-Dehydrocholesterol.description: 7-Dehydrocholesterol is a zoosterol that functions in the serum as a cholesterol precursor, and is converted to vitamin D3 in the skin, therefore functioning as provitamin-D3. Wikipedia

6-Phosphogluconolactone.label: 6-Phosphogluconolactone
6-Phosphogluconolactone.description:
6-Phosphogluconolactone is an intermediate in the pentose phosphate pathway.
It is produced from glucose-6-phosphate by glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase. Wikipedia

Acesulfame potassium.label: Acesulfame potassium
Acesulfame potassium.description: Acesulfame potassium is a calorie-free sugar substitute, also known as Acesulfame K or Ace K, and marketed under the trade names Sunett and Sweet One. In the European Union, it is known under the E number E950. Wikipedia

Absinthin.label: Absinthin
Absinthin.description: Absinthin is a naturally produced sesquiterpene lactone from the plant Artemisia absinthium. It constitutes one of the most bitter chemical agents responsible for Absinthe's distinct taste. Wikipedia

Acetochlor.label: Acetochlor
Acetochlor.description: Acetochlor is a herbicide developed by Monsanto Company and Zeneca. It is a member of the class of herbicides known as chloroacetanilides. Wikipedia

Acetone peroxide.label: Acetone peroxide
Acetone peroxide.description:
Acetone peroxide is an organic peroxide and a primary high explosive. It takes the form of a white crystalline powder with a distinctive bleach-like odor.
It is susceptible to heat, friction and shock. Wikipedia

Aconitine.label: Aconitine
Aconitine.description: Aconitine is a toxin produced by the Aconitum plant, also known as devil’s helmet or monkshood. Monkshood is very notorious for its toxic properties. In China, aconitine is also used as a herbal medicine against pain. Wikipedia

Acrylamide.label: Acrylamide
Acrylamide.description: Acrylamide is a chemical compound with the chemical formula C3H5NO. Its IUPAC name is prop-2-enamide. It is a white odourless crystalline solid, soluble in water, ethanol, ether, and chloroform. Wikipedia

Adamantane.label: Adamantane
Adamantane.description: Adamantane is a colorless, crystalline chemical compound with a camphor-like odor. With a formula C10H16, it is a cycloalkane and also the simplest diamondoid. Wikipedia

Allura Red AC.label: Allura Red AC
Allura Red AC.description: Allura Red AC is a red azo dye that goes by several names including Allura Red, Food Red 17, C.I. 16035, FD&C Red 40, E129, 2-naphthalenesulfonic acid, 6-hydroxy-5--, disodium salt, and disodium 6-hydroxy-5--2-naphthalenesulfonate. Wikipedia

Aluminium fluoride.label: Aluminium fluoride
Aluminium fluoride.description: Aluminium fluoride is an inorganic compound used primarily in the production of aluminium. This colorless solid can be prepared synthetically but also occurs in nature. It is used in the production of aluminium metal. Wikipedia

Allyl alcohol.label: Allyl alcohol
Allyl alcohol.description: Allyl alcohol is an organic compound with the structural formula CH2=CHCH2OH. Like many alcohols, it is a water-soluble, colourless liquid, but it is more toxic than typical small alcohols. Wikipedia

Aluminium iodide.label: Aluminium iodide
Aluminium iodide.description: Aluminium iodide is any chemical compound containing only aluminium and iodine. Invariably, the name refers to a compound of the composition AlI3, formed by the reaction of aluminium and iodine or the action of HI on Al metal. Wikipedia

Ammonium iron(III) sulfate.label: Ammonium iron(III) sulfate
Ammonium iron(III) sulfate.description: Ammonium iron(III) sulfate, NH4Fe(SO4)2·12 H2O, also known as ferric ammonium sulfate or iron alum, is a double salt in the class of alums, which consists of compounds with the general formula AB(SO4)2 · 12 H2O. Wikipedia

Ammonium perchlorate.label: Ammonium perchlorate
Ammonium perchlorate.description: Ammonium perchlorate is an inorganic compound with the formula NH4ClO4. It is the salt of perchloric acid and ammonia. It is a powerful oxidizer, which explains its main use in solid propellants. Wikipedia

Ammonium thiocyanate.label: Ammonium thiocyanate
Ammonium thiocyanate.description: Ammonium thiocyanate is an inorganic compound with the formula NH4SCN. It is the salt of the ammonium cation and the thiocyanate anion. Wikipedia

Ammonium thiosulfate.label: Ammonium thiosulfate
Ammonium thiosulfate.description: Ammonium thiosulfate is an inorganic compound. It is white crystalline solid with ammonia odor, readily soluble in water, slightly soluble in acetone and insoluble in ethanol and diethyl ether. Wikipedia

Amygdalin.label: Amygdalin
Amygdalin.description: Amygdalin, C20H27NO11, is a glycoside initially isolated from the seeds of the tree Prunus dulcis, also known as bitter almonds, by Pierre-Jean Robiquet and Antoine Boutron-Charlard, in 1830 and ... Wikipedia

Amyl nitrite.label: Amyl nitrite
Amyl nitrite.description: Amyl nitrite is the chemical compound with the formula C5H11ONO. A variety of isomers are known, but they all feature an amyl group attached to the nitrito functional group. Wikipedia

Anandamide.label: Anandamide
Anandamide.description: Anandamide, also known as N-arachidonoylethanolamine or AEA, is an endogenous cannabinoid neurotransmitter. The name is taken from the Sanskrit word ananda, which means "bliss, delight", and amide. Wikipedia

Anthracene.label: Anthracene
Anthracene.description: Anthracene is a solid polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon of formula C14H10, consisting of three fused benzene rings. It is a component of coal tar. Anthracene is used in the production of the red dye alizarin and other dyes. Wikipedia

Arabinose.label: Arabinose
Arabinose.description: Arabinose is an aldopentose – a monosaccharide containing five carbon atoms, and including an aldehyde functional group. Wikipedia

Ascaridole.label: Ascaridole
Ascaridole.description: Ascaridole is a natural organic compound classified as a bicyclic monoterpene that has an unusual bridging peroxide functional group. It is a colorless liquid with a pungent smell and taste that is soluble in most organic solvents. Wikipedia

Arsenic pentoxide.label: Arsenic pentoxide
Arsenic pentoxide.description: Arsenic pentoxide is the inorganic compound with the formula As2O5. This glassy, white, deliquescent solid is relatively unstable, consistent with the rarity of the As oxidation state. Wikipedia

Aurantinidin.label: Aurantinidin
Aurantinidin.description: Aurantinidin is a water soluble, red plant dye. It is a member of the class of compounds known as anthocyanidins and is a hydroxy derivative of pelargonidin. Wikipedia

Aziridine.label: Aziridine
Aziridine.description:
Aziridines are organic compounds containing the aziridine functional group, a three-membered heterocycle with one amine group and two methylene bridges. The parent compound is aziridine, with molecular formula C
2H
5N. Wikipedia

Azobenzene.label: Azobenzene
Azobenzene.description: Azobenzene is a chemical compound composed of two phenyl rings linked by a N=N double bond. It is the simplest example of an azo compound. Wikipedia

Barium borate.label: Barium borate
Barium borate.description: Barium borate is an inorganic compound, a borate of barium with a chemical formula BaB2O4 or Ba(BO2)2. It is available as a hydrate or dehydrated form, as white powder or colorless crystals. Wikipedia

Azorubine.label: Azorubine
Azorubine.description: Azorubine, carmoisine, Food Red 3, Azorubin S, Brillantcarmoisin O, Acid Red 14, or C.I. 14720 is a synthetic red food dye from the azo dye group. It usually comes as a disodium salt. It is a red to maroon powder. Wikipedia

Barium chromate.label: Barium chromate
Barium chromate.description: Barium chromate, named barium tetraoxochromate by the IUPAC, is a yellow sand like powder with the formula BaCrO4. It is a known oxidizing agent and produces a green flame when heated, a result of the barium ions. Wikipedia

Barium fluoride.label: Barium fluoride
Barium fluoride.description: Barium fluoride is a chemical compound of barium and fluorine. It is a solid which can be a transparent crystal. It occurs in nature as the mineral frankdicksonite. Wikipedia

Barium peroxide.label: Barium peroxide
Barium peroxide.description: Barium peroxide is the inorganic compound with the formula BaO2. This white solid is one of the most common inorganic peroxides. Wikipedia

Bendiocarb.label: Bendiocarb
Bendiocarb.description: Bendiocarb is an acutely toxic carbamate insecticide used in public health and agriculture and is effective against a wide range of nuisance and disease vector insects. Wikipedia

Bensulide.label: Bensulide
Bensulide.description: Bensulide is an organophosphate acetylcholinesterase inhibitor used as an herbicide. It functions by inhibiting cell division in meristematic root tissues and seedling growth by conjugation of acetyl co-enzyme. Wikipedia

Benzamide.label: Benzamide
Benzamide.description: Benzamide is an off-white solid with the chemical formula of C6H5CONH2. It is a derivative of benzoic acid. It is slightly soluble in water, and soluble in many organic solvents. Wikipedia

Benzidine.label: Benzidine
Benzidine.description: Benzidine, also called 4,4'-diaminobiphenyl, is the organic compound with the formula (C6H4NH2)2. it is an aromatic amine. It is a component of a test for cyanide. Related derivatives are used in the production of dyes. Wikipedia

Benzimidazole.label: Benzimidazole
Benzimidazole.description: Benzimidazole is a heterocyclic aromatic organic compound. This bicyclic compound consists of the fusion of benzene and imidazole. Wikipedia

Benzofuran.label: Benzofuran
Benzofuran.description: Benzofuran is the heterocyclic compound consisting of fused benzene and furan rings. This colourless liquid is a component of coal tar. Benzofuran is the "parent" of many related compounds with more complex structures. Wikipedia

Beryllium chloride.label: Beryllium chloride
Beryllium chloride.description: Beryllium chloride is an inorganic compound with the formula BeCl2. It is a colourless, hygroscopic solid that dissolves well in many polar solvents. Wikipedia

Benzothiazole.label: Benzothiazole
Benzothiazole.description:
Benzothiazole is an aromatic heterocyclic compound with the chemical formula C
7H
5NS. It is colorless, slightly viscous liquid. Wikipedia

Beta-Methylamino-L-alanine.label: beta-Methylamino-L-alanine
Beta-Methylamino-L-alanine.description: β-Methylamino-L-alanine, or BMAA, is a non-proteinogenic amino acid produced by cyanobacteria. Wikipedia

Beta-Hydroxy beta-methylbutyric acid.label: beta-Hydroxy beta-methylbutyric acid
Beta-Hydroxy beta-methylbutyric acid.description: β-Hydroxy β-methylbutyric acid, or β-hydroxy β-methylbutyrate, is a metabolite of the essential amino acid leucine and is synthesized in the human body. Its part in protein synthesis was discovered by Steven L. Nissen at Iowa State University. Wikipedia

Betulinic acid.label: Betulinic acid
Betulinic acid.description: Betulinic acid is a naturally occurring pentacyclic triterpenoid which has antiretroviral, antimalarial, and anti-inflammatory properties, as well as a more recently discovered potential as an anticancer agent, by inhibition of topoisomerase. Wikipedia

Bialaphos.label: Bialaphos
Bialaphos.description: Bialaphos is a natural herbicide produced by the bacteria Streptomyces hygroscopicus and Streptomyces viridochromeogenes. Wikipedia

Bifenthrin.label: Bifenthrin
Bifenthrin.description: Bifenthrin is a pyrethroid insecticide used primarily against the red imported fire ant by influencing its nerve system. It has a high toxicity to aquatic organisms. Wikipedia

Biguanide.label: Biguanide
Biguanide.description: Biguanide is the organic compound with the formula HN(C(NH)NH2)2. It is a colourless solid that dissolves in water to give highly basic solution. These solutions slowly hydrolyse to ammonia and urea. Wikipedia

Biliverdin.label: Biliverdin
Biliverdin.description: Biliverdin is a green tetrapyrrolic bile pigment, and is a product of heme catabolism. It is the pigment responsible for a greenish color sometimes seen in bruises. Wikipedia

Bisabolol.label: Bisabolol
Bisabolol.description: Bisabolol, or more formally α--bisabolol or also known as levomenol, is a natural monocyclic sesquiterpene alcohol. It is a colorless viscous oil that is the primary constituent of the essential oil from German chamomile and Myoporum crassifolium. Wikipedia

Bismuth(III) sulfide.label: Bismuth(III) sulfide
Bismuth(III) sulfide.description: Bismuth(III) sulfide is a chemical compound of bismuth and sulfur. It occurs in nature as the mineral bismuthinite. Wikipedia

Bismuth(III) oxide.label: Bismuth(III) oxide
Bismuth(III) oxide.description: Bismuth(III) oxide is perhaps the most industrially important compound of bismuth. It is also a common starting point for bismuth chemistry. Wikipedia

Bismuthine.label: Bismuthine
Bismuthine.description: Bismuthine is the chemical compound with the formula BiH3. As the heaviest analogue of ammonia, BiH3 is unstable, decomposing to bismuth metal well below 0 °C. This compound adopts the expected pyramidal structure with H-Bi-H angles of around 90°. Wikipedia

Bradykinin.label: Bradykinin
Bradykinin.description: Bradykinin is a peptide that causes blood vessels to dilate, and therefore causes blood pressure to lower. A class of drugs called ACE inhibitors, which are used to lower blood pressure, increase bradykinin further lowering blood pressure. Wikipedia

Bromoxynil.label: Bromoxynil
Bromoxynil.description: Bromoxynil is a nitrile herbicide, trade names include Brominal, Bromotril, Bronate, Buctril, Certrol B, Litarol, M&B 10064, Merit, Pardner, Sabre, and Torch. It is used for post-emergent control of annual broadleaf weeds. Wikipedia

C-peptide.label: C-peptide
C-peptide.description: The connecting peptide, or C-peptide, is a short 31-amino-acid protein that connects insulin's A-chain to its B-chain in the proinsulin molecule. Wikipedia

Caesium chloride.label: Caesium chloride
Caesium chloride.description: Caesium chloride or cesium chloride, is the inorganic compound with the formula CsCl. This colorless solid is an important source of caesium ions in a variety of applications. Wikipedia

Caesium fluoride.label: Caesium fluoride
Caesium fluoride.description: Caesium fluoride or cesium fluoride is an inorganic compound usually encountered as a hygroscopic white solid. It is used in organic synthesis as a source of the fluoride anion. Wikipedia

Calcium bicarbonate.label: Calcium bicarbonate
Calcium bicarbonate.description: Calcium bicarbonate, also called calcium hydrogen carbonate, has a chemical formula Ca(HCO3)2. The term does not refer to a known solid compound; it exists only in aqueous solution containing the calcium, ... Wikipedia

Caesium oxide.label: Caesium oxide
Caesium oxide.description: Caesium oxide or cesium oxide describes inorganic compounds composed of caesium and oxygen. The following binary oxides of caesium are known Cs11O3, Cs4O, Cs7O, and Cs2O. Both the oxide and suboxides are brightly coloured. Wikipedia

Calcium hypochlorite.label: Calcium hypochlorite
Calcium hypochlorite.description: Calcium hypochlorite is a chemical compound with formula Ca(ClO)2. It is widely used for water treatment and as a bleaching agent. This chemical is considered to be relatively stable and has greater available chlorine than sodium hypochlorite. Wikipedia

Canavanine.label: Canavanine
Canavanine.description: L---Canavanine is a non-proteinogenic α-amino acid found in certain leguminous plants. It is structurally related to the proteinogenic α-amino acid L-arginine, the sole difference being the replacement ... Wikipedia

Cantharidin.label: Cantharidin
Cantharidin.description: Cantharidin, a type of terpenoid, is a chemical compound secreted by many species of blister beetle, and most notably by the Spanish fly, Lytta vesicatoria. The false blister beetles, cardinal beetles and soldier beetles also produce cantharidin. Wikipedia

Carbazole.label: Carbazole
Carbazole.description: Carbazole is an aromatic heterocyclic organic compound. It has a tricyclic structure, consisting of two six-membered benzene rings fused on either side of a five-membered nitrogen-containing ring. Wikipedia

Caprolactam.label: Caprolactam
Caprolactam.description: Caprolactam is an organic compound with the formula (CH2)5CNH. This colourless solid is a lactam or a cyclic amide of caproic acid. Approximately 4.5 billion kilograms are produced annually. Wikipedia

Carbethopendecinium bromide.label: Carbethopendecinium bromide
Carbethopendecinium bromide.description: Carbethopendecinium bromide is a quaternary ammonium compound used as antiseptic and disinfectant. It is white to yellowish crystalline powder. It is well soluble in water, ethanol and chloroform; its water solutions foam strongly if shaken. Wikipedia

Carbofuran.label: Carbofuran
Carbofuran.description: Carbofuran is one of the most toxic carbamate pesticides. It is marketed under the trade names Furadan, by FMC Corporation and Curater, among several others. Wikipedia

Carbosulfan.label: Carbosulfan
Carbosulfan.description: Carbosulfan is an organic compound adherent to the carbamate class. At normal conditions, it is brown viscose liquid. It is not very stable; it decomposes slowly at room temperature. Wikipedia

Carbon tetraiodide.label: Carbon tetraiodide
Carbon tetraiodide.description: Carbon tetraiodide is CI4, a tetrahalomethane. Being bright red, it is a relatively rare example of a highly colored methane derivative. It is only 2% by weight carbon, although other methane derivatives are known with still less carbon. Wikipedia

Carmustine.label: Carmustine
Carmustine.description: Treats brain tumors, multiple myeloma, Hodgkin's disease, non-Hodgkin's lymphoma, and other types of cancer.Implantation Side effects - Warnings - How to useInjection Side effects - Warnings - How to use National Library of Medicine

Carvacrol.label: Carvacrol
Carvacrol.description: Carvacrol, or cymophenol, C6H3CH3, is a monoterpenoid phenol. It has a characteristic pungent, warm odor of oregano. Wikipedia

Cellobiose.label: Cellobiose
Cellobiose.description: Cellobiose is a disaccharide with the formula [HOCH2CHO(CHOH)3]2O. Cellobiose consists of two glucose molecules linked by a β bond. It can be hydrolyzed to glucose enzymatically or with acid. Wikipedia

Chlordane.label: Chlordane
Chlordane.description: Chlordane, or chlordan, is an organochlorine compound used as a pesticide. This white solid was sold in the U.S. until 1983 as an insecticide for crops like corn and citrus, and on lawns and domestic gardens. Wikipedia

Cetylpyridinium chloride.label: Cetylpyridinium chloride
Cetylpyridinium chloride.description: Cetylpyridinium chloride is a cationic quaternary ammonium compound used in some types of mouthwashes, toothpastes, lozenges, throat sprays, breath sprays, and nasal sprays. It is an antiseptic that kills bacteria and other microorganisms. Wikipedia

Chloroprene.label: Chloroprene
Chloroprene.description: Chloroprene is the common name for the organic compound 2-chlorobuta-1,3-diene, which has the formula CH2=CCl-CH=CH2. This colorless liquid is the monomer for the production of the polymer polychloroprene, a type of synthetic rubber. Wikipedia

Cholecalciferol.label: Cholecalciferol
Cholecalciferol.description:
Cholecalciferol is a form of vitamin D, also called vitamin D3.
It is structurally similar to steroids such as testosterone, cholesterol, and cortisol. Wikipedia

Cholic acid.label: Cholic acid
Cholic acid.description: Cholic acid is a bile acid, a white crystalline substance insoluble in water, with a melting point of 200-201 °C. Salts of cholic acid are called cholates. Wikipedia

Chorismic acid.label: Chorismic acid
Chorismic acid.description: Chorismic acid, more commonly known as its anionic form chorismate, is an important biochemical intermediate in plants and microorganisms. Wikipedia

Chromium(IV) oxide.label: Chromium(IV) oxide
Chromium(IV) oxide.description: Chromium dioxide or chromium(IV) oxide is a synthetic magnetic substance once widely used in magnetic tape emulsion. With the increasing popularity of CDs and DVDs, the use of chromium(IV) oxide has declined. Wikipedia

Chromium nitrate.label: Chromium nitrate
Chromium nitrate.description: Chromium nitrate describes several inorganic compounds consisting of chromium, nitrate and varying amounts of water. Most common is the dark violet hydrated solid, but an anhydrous green form is also known. Wikipedia

Cinnamaldehyde.label: Cinnamaldehyde
Cinnamaldehyde.description: Cinnamaldehyde is the organic compound that gives cinnamon its flavor and odor. This pale yellow, viscous liquid occurs naturally in the bark of cinnamon trees and other species of the genus Cinnamomum. Wikipedia
